            <fr:title text="Radon Probability Measure">Radon Probability Measure</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
A <html:strong>Radon probability measure</html:strong> on a <fr:link href="/gtop-000O/" title="Locally Compact Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000O/" display-uri="gtop-000O" type="local">locally compact</fr:link> <fr:link href="/gtop-000B/" title="Hausdorff Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000B/" display-uri="gtop-000B" type="local">Hausdorff space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/gtop-000A/" title="Radon Measure" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000A/" display-uri="gtop-000A" type="local">Radon measure</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu ]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu (X) = 1]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
The space of all Radon probability measures on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}(X)]]></fr:tex>. When <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/gtop-0008/" title="Compactness" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/" display-uri="gtop-0008" type="local">compact</fr:link> <fr:link href="/gtop-0009/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0009/" display-uri="gtop-0009" type="local">metric space</fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}(X)]]></fr:tex> equipped with the weak-* topology is itself a compact metric space.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
